headline: Apple has asked suppliers to boost production of iPhone 17 model, the Information reports
summary: The development suggests more consumers than Apple anticipated chose the cheaper $799 iPhone 17 over the premium Pro models, which start at $1,099 and typically offer superior materials, cameras, processors and displays.  Apple this week asked Luxshare Precision, one of its two main iPhone assemblers in China, alongside Foxconn, to boost daily output of the standard iPhone 17 by about 40%, the report said.  Apple did not immediately respond to a Reuters request for comment.

headline: OpenAI taps Apple supplier to make AI device, the Information reports
summary: The device is currently a prototype under development and is expected to be pocket-sized and aware of context, designed to work closely with the ChatGPT parent's artificial intelligence models.  Such a gadget could eat into the markets of Apple and other consumer electronics makers by offering an alternative to users for interacting with AI, challenging the dominance of smartphones and traditional hardware.  OpenAI bought hardware startup io Products, founded by former Apple designer Jony Ive, earlier this year in a $6.5 billion deal, underscoring its push to move beyond software into consumer hardware.
